  m_Name: 8. QueueActionTut
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  dialogue:
  - bodyText: Targeting an enemy adds the Action to the battle queue.
    speakerName: Ives
    displayingImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 1196bb0135ba2a645ada67564f0da12f, type: 3}
    sfx: 
    broadcastAnEvent: 0
  - bodyText: The queue is sorted by Speed, with the fastest on the left.
    speakerName: Ives
    displayingImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 1196bb0135ba2a645ada67564f0da12f, type: 3}
    sfx: 
    broadcastAnEvent: 0
  - bodyText: You can [Hover] over a queued card's icon to check its stats again.
    speakerName: Ives
    displayingImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 57baba5992d9e224988e93fcacf9f7eb, type: 3}
    sfx: 
    broadcastAnEvent: 0
  - bodyText: Or [Left Click] it to pull it back into your hand.
    speakerName: Ives
    displayingImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 57baba5992d9e224988e93fcacf9f7eb, type: 3}
    sfx: 
    broadcastAnEvent: 0
  - bodyText: Each round, you can queue up as many Actions as you'd like. However...
    speakerName: Ives
    displayingImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 57baba5992d9e224988e93fcacf9f7eb, type: 3}
    sfx: 
    broadcastAnEvent: 0
  - bodyText: "You can\u2019t play two Actions that share the same Speed."
    speakerName: Ives
    displayingImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: b1411cc1e1231574797f223a58264863, type: 3}
    sfx: 
    broadcastAnEvent: 0
  - bodyText: If a card turns red, that means another Action with the same Speed
      is already queued.
    speakerName: Ives
    displayingImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 37984fb1d201d1246a4e2a0ac7061427, type: 3}
    sfx: 
    broadcastAnEvent: 0
  - bodyText: Once you're confident in your setup, press Confirm to start combat.
    speakerName: Ives
    displayingImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: ac6eebf9323f6405fb24f7403fc43497, type: 3}
    sfx: 
    broadcastAnEvent: 0
